The paper deals with consensus seeking systems, which are typically studied in the control theory and systems engineering literature, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses evolving interaction topologies, which are a common feature in multi-agent systems, falling under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses convergence properties of the system, which is a common theme in dynamical systems theory, falling under the category of dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of random or endogenously determined interaction topologies, which is a common theme in network science, falling under the category of network science (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of continuous and discrete-time systems, which is a common theme in signal processing and control theory, falling under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
